CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1775952175
OL,3,CGolden eagles could be reintroduced to
OL,4,CEngland with new funding, ministers say
OL,6,FA study by Forestry England, published
OL,7,Fon Sunday, found that England now has
OL,8,Fthe capacity to sustain golden eagle
OL,9,Fpopulations again.
OL,11,FThe paper identified eight potential
OL,12,F"recovery zones" as the most suitable
OL,13,Fareas, mostly in the north of England,
OL,14,Falthough it could take more than a
OL,15,Fdecade until breeding populations are
OL,16,Festablished in the area.
OL,18,FIn response, Environment Secretary
OL,19,FEmma Reynolds approved #1 million in
OL,20,Fadditional funding to help pave the
OL,21,Fway for a recovery programme.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
